Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded 110 mln dlrs of debt of Michigan General Corp.    Reduced were the company's 10-3/4 pct senior subordinateddebentures of 1998 to Caa from B-3.    Moody's cited Michigan's ongoing losses which have impairedliquidity, weakened financial flexibility and lessened thelikelihood for operating performance to improve.    Michigan's principal business, lumber and housebuildingproducts sales, operates in a cyclical and highly competitveenvironment so that even debt restructuring would probably notimprove earnings, Moody's pointed out. Reuter&#3;